<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  vibemix — macOS Hardened Runtime entitlements
  Bundle ID: world.bravoh.vibemix (LOCKED — see 11-RESEARCH.md A8)

  [VERIFIED: 11-RESEARCH.md §Phase 11 specific security checklist (lines 1415-1425)]
  [VERIFIED: Apple Hardened Runtime docs — https://developer.apple.com/documentation/security/hardened_runtime]

  Phase 11 Wave 1 — authored alongside the PyInstaller spec so the wave's
  packaging story is complete in one place. Phase 18 codesigns the final
  bundle WITH this entitlements file via:
      codesign --force --options runtime --entitlements tauri/src-tauri/entitlements.plist ...

  WHY each entitlement is required:

  - audio-input + microphone: the wizard's Step 1 prompts mic permission;
    the live session listens to BlackHole loopback + Kaan's mic for the
    KAAN_SPOKE detector.
  - allow-unsigned-executable-memory: PyInstaller bootloader runs C
    extensions (scipy, numpy, sounddevice native libs) that allocate
    executable memory pages outside the bundle's signed code segment.
    Without this, Hardened Runtime kills the process on first audio frame.
  - disable-library-validation: livekit-rtc + google-genai + sounddevice
    dynamically load .dylib files from PyInstaller's onedir tree. Those
    .dylibs are signed by their upstreams, not by Bravoh. Hardened Runtime
    refuses to load them unless this entitlement is set. This is the
    accepted PyInstaller-on-macOS pattern (Tauri docs §macOS distribution +
    PyInstaller GH discussions).

  WHAT IS DELIBERATELY NOT INCLUDED:

  - allow-jit: we don't run a JIT. Python bytecode is interpreted; numpy /
    scipy use AOT-compiled C — no JIT entitlement needed.
  - allow-arbitrary-loads: we have a strict allowlist (Phase 5 proxy at
    api.altidus.world + GitHub for autoupdate). Anything else is rejected
    by the Tauri capability config in Wave 2.
  - camera / address-book / location / get-task-allow: zero use cases.

  THREAT MODEL (per 11-02-PLAN.md):
  T-11-W1-03 (Spoofing — localhost binding): accepted; localhost
  single-user. Codesigning with this entitlements list pins the bundle
  identity so the OS can detect tampering.
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Audio capture: BlackHole loopback (master) + Kaan's mic -->
    <key>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.device.microphone</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- PyInstaller bootloader + C-ext native libs need writable+executable
         memory pages outside the signed code segment. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- LiveKit / Gemini / sounddevice load third-party .dylibs that are
         signed by their upstreams but not by Bravoh's identity. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
